This is cute but of course horribly unsafe since it doesn&#x27;t respect control statements.<p>Some examples you&#x27;d expect to work that will crash the interpreter:<p><pre><code>  @with_goto
  def fun1():
   while True:
    for x in [1]:
     goto .next
    label .next

  @with_goto
  def fun2():
   goto .next
   for x in [1]:
    label .next

  @with_goto
  def fun3():
   while True:
    try:
     goto .next
    finally:
     print(&#x27;skipped&#x27;)
    label .next</code></pre>
